				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Donations welcome<a name="16501"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 21 04 3:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I rarely request donations, but I need to do so this month. I need funds to make my big move this week. I've also been working non-stop on EQDiva to help bring you a top-notch class site. See the &quot;Donate&quot; link to the left, or use the Paypal icon on the EZBoard forums. Also, you can support EQDiva by shopping Amazon by hitting my site first (See &quot;EQDiva Bazaar&quot; which is just a start).
<br />

<br />
For the past few year or so, EQDiva has been free, I tried cancelling the site a long time ago, and it seems that the web hosting company overlooked this, yet kept the site up without charge (they wanted to charge me $500/mo before I cancelled). All the work I've been doing was on my personal site, so I haven't been asking for donations as the site was free. The dotnetdiva site cost me $45/mo, but I am way exceeding my bandwidth and database storage, so I have to find a new home.
<br />

<br />
It's now time to move EQDiva back home. I found a new web hosting company and it is perfect for my needs. While some companies want to charge me $200-500/mo to host the site, I found one that meets all my needs, and my site falls within their requirements of their highest level of shared hosting. I even got a great deal! The monthly cost is $65 plus a $50 setup fee. 
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.interland.com/shared/bluehalo/?package=b300&amp;page=b300&amp;path=snavb300">http://www.interland.com/shared/bluehalo/?package=b300&amp;page=b300&amp;path=snavb300</a>
<br />

<br />
Some may chip in and say they could host me for $15 or something like that, but I have requirements being a 100MB+ SQL Server storage, unlimited bandwidth, and .NET 1.1, Site statistics, Mobile Internet kit (to provide EQDiva on cellphone in future), as well as a whole host of techie goodies I need. So $65 a month covers hosting, database, and forums, and I think that's a great deal! 
<br />

<br />
So I'd like to request donations as I move EQDiva to her new web host. Please only donate if you are able to do so, and there's no minimum donation, every dollar is appreciated. 
<br />

<br />
If you donate via Paypal, please include your EQDiva username (or EZboard name if you're not registered yet) and your bard name and I'll add you to the EQDiva Supporters page I'm working on. If you'd rather remain anonymous, also please indicate.
<br />

<br />
And thank you, thank you to all those who have ever donated!
<br />

<br />
