				<td colspan="2"><span>1planhost does look awesome, and I will refer it to folks looking for a cheap .NET web host! But they have lots of addons for what I need, and it would be alot more than $99/year. And that company only offers 20gb bandwidth a month, which is alot, but not enough for us.
<br />

<br />
I need a very solid web hosting company. I've hosted with free sites (ICK), sites that were only $15/mo, and hosts that wanted $500/mo out of me. I've worked on alot of sites, both personal and commercial, and nothing beats this company I chose in terms of value and features. If you want EQDiva to be up and running most of the time, and running fast, then we have to go with something that costs more than $10/mo unfortunately.
<br />

<br />
It's hard to find web hosts under $60/mo that offer 100MB+ SQL Server database storage, stored procedures, code components, unlimited bandwidth (no mp3s, warez, adult stuff), web statistics, Web site admin panel, and has an uptime of 99.999%. I've spent four years studying the best solution for EQDiva to host on, and I'm very happy with my decision. In fact, I think it won't be long before I have to pay twice as much as I do now due to the database storage, I'm limited in my plans for information right now, and I'd love to add new features, but not sure if it's worth it.
<br />

<br />
My requirements are high, this is a major application, not just a bunch of scripts. This is a multi-tier enterprise application built for performance, and is similar to what I would work on in some of my past huge clients like Best Buy, Honeywell, or Internet companies like BigCharts.com, CBS Marketwatch, and online loan application companies. 
<br />

<br />
Well, I could chat all day on this topic, so I'll just say that I've looked into everything and I feel this is the best solution.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
